article_title: Amber Alert Canceled For Ottumwa, IA Teen
article_text:
Ottumwa, IA

The Amber Alert issued by Iowa authorities for a 13-year-old Ottumwa girl has been canceled.

According to the Iowa Department of Transportation, Paige Johnstone and 19-year-old Kevin Ramirez were found safe in Georgia Saturday afternoon.

Johnstone left home with Ramirez Saturday. Authorities say Ramirez has a criminal record.

They were last seen driving a yellow 2001 Nissan Frontier with Florida license plate #ERZB06. They were believed to be heading to Fort Pierce, Florida.
